parameters.text:
=Analyze this Jira bug ticket and identify:
1. Testing scope - what needs to be tested
2. Affected modules - which parts of the system are impacted
3. Risk areas - what could go wrong
4. Required test types - functional, UI, integration, regression, etc.
5. Dependencies - what systems or components are involved

Ticket: {{ $json.ticketKey }}
Summary: {{ $json.summary }}
Description: {{ $json.description }}
Priority: {{ $json.priority }}
Type: {{ $json.issueType }}

parameters.jsonSchemaExample:
{
  "testingScope": "Mobile login functionality",
  "affectedModules": [
    "Authentication",
    "Mobile UI"
  ],
  "riskAreas": [
    "User access",
    "Security"
  ],
  "requiredTestTypes": [
    "Functional",
    "UI",
    "Regression"
  ],
  "dependencies": [
    "Mobile app",
    "Authentication service"
  ]
}

parameters.text:
=Create a comprehensive professional test plan document based on this analysis.

Ticket: {{ $("Extract Ticket Data").item.json.ticketKey }}
Summary: {{ $("Extract Ticket Data").item.json.summary }}
Priority: {{ $("Extract Ticket Data").item.json.priority }}

Analysis:
Testing Scope: {{ $json.output.testingScope }}
Affected Modules: {{ $json.output.affectedModules }}
Risk Areas: {{ $json.output.riskAreas }}
Required Test Types: {{ $json.output.requiredTestTypes }}
Dependencies: {{ $json.output.dependencies }}

Include:
1. Test Objectives
2. Test Strategy
3. Scope (In-scope and Out-of-scope)
4. Entry and Exit Criteria
5. Severity Analysis (Critical/High/Medium/Low)
6. Priority Classification
7. Business Impact Assessment
8. Test Environment Requirements
9. Risks and Mitigation

Format as a professional document with clear sections.

parameters.jsonSchemaExample:
